Presenting "Jumla," a soulful tune with a love story at its core. The words for this song were written by Aman Neelsagar and me. I composed the song, produced it, and performed it. Many aspects of Karnali Province and far-western culture, including the Khas dialect, can be found in this song. This swoon-worthy tune features Miss Pabi and Roshan KC. This music video was filmed across Jumla in several stunning settings. The music video is directed by Shishir Khati.

Duniyadari Episode 739.
In this episode, Divyanshi talks about the new prime minister of Nepal Pushpa Kamal Dahal 'Prachanda' and the shaky politics of Nepal.

Pushpa Kamal Dahal ‚ÄúPrachanda‚Äù was sworn in as Nepal‚Äôs new Prime Minister on Monday after he switched sides to join hands with a bitter foe, former prime minister Kharga Prasad Oli. This is Prachanda‚Äôs third stint as the head of government in the 14 years since Nepal‚Äôs monarchy was abolished. Before joining mainstream politics in 2006, he had led the Maoist revolt in Nepal for over a decade.

- What is the full story of Prachanda, the new Prime Minister of Nepal?
- What is the Story behind this general election?
- what will be the effect on India after Prachanda becomes the Prime Minister of Nepal?

We also asked the Senior Journalist Prem Punetha and Yubaraj Ghimire about Prachanda's political career and the future of Nepal Politics.

Prem Punetha is a senior journalist and has extensively covered Nepal's aftermath of the Civil War.

Yubaraj Ghimire is a veteran journalist and has been covering Nepal for 39 years. He is based in Kathmandu. He is also a columnist for Indian Express. In the past, He has worked with various Indian publications--The Telegraph (daily) and Sunday Magazine, India Today as its special correspondent, Assistant Editor of Outlook Magazine, and Associate Editor of Indian Express. After that, He joined BBC (Language service) for a couple of years. He could be reached on Twitter (@YubarajGhimire3).

snippet.title: The Kapil Sharma Show Season 2 | Kapil Ke Show Mei Hui Cirkus | Ep 288 | FE | 17 Dec 2022
snippet.description:
Synopsis: Kapil Ke Show Mei Hui Cirkus
 --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
The host, Kapil Sharma makes a rocking entry to the stage and welcomes everyone to the show. He then proceeds to welcome the special guests for the night. They are none other than the star cast of the upcoming comedy film, Cirkus, starring Ranveer Singh, Jacqueline Fernandez, Pooja Hegde, and Varun Sharma. They are here to promote their film along with their director, Rohit Shetty who tells that the lead character was inspired by Ranveer's real-life personality and energy. To witness more, watch the episode now.

Show Name: The Kapil Sharma Show Season 2
Guest Names: Ranveer Singh, Rohit Shetty, Jacqueline Fernandez, Pooja Hegde, Varun Sharma.
Host: Kapil Sharma, Archana Puran Singh
Episode: 288 - 12 Dec 2022
Producers: Kapil Sharma

snippet.description:
Meri Bassai is one of the longest and most popular Nepali comedy serials with 17 Years of broadcasting. Based on rural lifestyle and lower-middle-class people, the series represents many political and social issues on its episodes with educational comedy flavor. It is aired in Nepal Television at 8:50 PM and in YouTube at 9:30 PM every Tuesday. This show is produced by Media Hub Pvt. Ltd. 

The story is based on the rural lifestyle and lower-middle-class people. The show represents many political as well as social issues on its episodes with educational comedy flavour.

en.description:
Meri Bassai is one of the longest and most popular Nepali comedy serials with 17 Years of broadcasting. Based on rural lifestyle and lower-middle-class people, the series represents many political and social issues on its episodes with educational comedy flavor. It is aired in Nepal Television at 8:50 PM and in YouTube at 9:30 PM every Tuesday. This show is produced by Media Hub Pvt. Ltd. 

The story is based on the rural lifestyle and lower-middle-class people. The show represents many political as well as social issues on its episodes with educational comedy flavour.
